---
layout: base.njk
title: Home
templateClass: home
---
<section class="hero">
  <p>I'm Mani Kumar Kundurthi — I work in data science and quantitative modeling, and write here as I work through machine learning, coding, and mathematics.</p>
  <p>This is a running notebook, not a polished blog: derivations, implementation notes, and things I wanted to understand properly rather than skim past. Read the <a href="{{ '/about/' | url }}">about page</a> for more.</p>
</section>

<h2 class="index-heading">Articles</h2>

<div class="article-scroll">
{% if collections.articles.length %}
<ul class="article-list">
  {% for article in collections.articles %}
  <li class="article-entry">
    <span class="entry-index">{{ (loop.length - loop.index0) | pad2 }}</span>
    <div class="entry-body">
      <a href="{{ article.url | url }}" class="entry-title">{{ article.data.title }}</a>
      <div class="entry-meta">
        <time datetime="{{ article.data.date | isoDate }}">{{ article.data.date | readableDate }}</time>
        {% for tag in article.data.tags %}
          {% if tag != "articles" %}<span class="entry-tag">{{ tag }}</span>{% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
      {% if article.data.summary %}<p class="entry-summary">{{ article.data.summary }}</p>{% endif %}
    </div>
  </li>
  {% endfor %}
</ul>
{% else %}
<p class="empty-note">No articles published yet — check back soon.</p>
{% endif %}
</div>
